76561198176513125,Recommended,214360,17397465,"Posted: 5 August, 2015",all,Bro für die Welt,"In short: This is an AWESOME multiplayer tower defense game, but not too many people play it, so you should convince your friends to get it. You need a few hours to master all the mechanics, but then it's great entertainment.You and your opponent both have castles and barracks, and you need to send waves to destroy each other, while simultaneously upgrading your units and castles as well as tending to your gold mines. Gold is mainly needed for recruiting units, and as long as they are within enemy territory, they earn ""battle points"" for you, which you need for upgrades. This makes for some challenging gameplay, as you need gold to earn battle points, but also battle points to get upgrades to earn more gold, ...There are many different units, each with unique attributes - speed, health, damage dealt (against opponent's castle), armor, shield. Some have special abilities, e.g. they increase other units' speed or improve their shields.Similarly, there are lots of different towers with unique strengths and weaknesses, e.g. arrow towers, cannons, lava distributors, fans (to slow down the enemy's units) etc.There are a few maps shipped with the game and you can download additional maps from the community. The gold mines are always placed randomly, which means that for every match, you need to come up with a new path around which to build your defense towers (although you will always be using the same basic structures).I recommend that you buy this on sale and get additional keys for your friends, because as mentioned above, it's hard to even find opponents for multiplayer, and the matching can take ages. But I have spent way too many hours playing against buddies now and we're all hooked!PROS:[+] Challenging game mechanics[+] Awesome multiplayer mode (1v1, 2v2, 3v3)[+] Many maps to choose from and random adjustments in each round[+] Very cool steampunk settingCONS:[-] Steep learning curve (although this becomes rewarding if you don't give up early)[-] Very few people ""out there"" for multiplayer matches (but it's more fun with friends anyway)[-] Boring co-op mode"
