,Recommended,214360,8381618,"Posted: 28 December, 2013",all,Lex Lagger,"Tower Wars,It's not your average tower defence game. Sure it has a survival mode to play it that way but that's not the sole action of this game. It's a tower defender and attacker! That's right you have to go on the offence or no matter how great you planning if you only defend you will fail. In fact if your balance of attach vs defence is even a little off you will fail. The computer baddys are tough, and may even break you heh.The real grabber with this game though is the online portion. You can battle with or against friends and strangers from across the world. Yes I used the plural, you can join with up to two other people per team (3 total) for a 6 player game! This is a fantasticly fun way to play. Mixing more than one mind into the game makes it a lot of fun, and a bit more challenging. Things happen fast, so don't plan on a extended set up period. A game can be completed in just a few turns or it can last for up to an hour (In one battle I had so far) all depending on the skill level and a little bit of luck in mine placements which are always random.The good:Instant funDecent ""Cartoony"" graphicssmooth, lag free playPlay with friends!New exciting twist to the tower defence genreThe bad:Can be a little slow to loadYou don't get the option to ""Rematch"" and the game quits out on it's own after a match. So no chanceto ask the other player to a hosted battle for a rematch either.The above makes meeting new people that play and growing your circle in the game a bit harder than it should be.You can always use the steam ""Recently Played"" list but you shouldn't have to."
