,Recommended,214360,7584363,"Posted: 6 November, 2013",all,Fohmyn,"If you're a fan of the tower defense genre, Tower Wars is a surprisingly good offering. I must warn that it is primarily head-to-head tower defense, so none of the storyline or RPG tie-ins that other titles offer. Still, it's very well-made and is a great example of the genre. You build towers to channel and kill enemies, while balancing resource production, units to pressure your enemy, your defenses, and upgrading your units to do more damage. It's a pretty interesting priority based system where every game plays out very differently based on how you and your opponent react. The way it makes me think is more like a RTS than a tower defense game. Pretty good."
