,Recommended,214360,8626750,"Posted: 8 January, 2014",all,Grognard_87,"I find I have a lot of fun with this game. Tower Wars is a challenging tower-defence game, but with a twist where in one game mode you can send out armies to attack the enemy to gain battle tokens. Even if they don't reach they castle, you get tokens based on how far they go.I find it enjoyable, even when losing which is easy if you don't get a good balance of putting up towers, shaping the path, putting up the right de-buffing towers and so on. It's cartoonish effects make the game a lot of fun t play and there are 10 levels of difficulty to play, though from what I can tell no actual story in the game itself.However a big complaint I have is that it seems to be prone to crashing. I'm uncertain if this is a common factor on other people's systems, but it does seem to be prone to crashing, though when it does crash it just closes rarther than going black screen or forcing steam to crash which tells me it's possibly being worked on in patches. Still, it is quite a enjoyable game and I recommend you give it a go if you are a fan of tower-defence games."
