,Recommended,214360,13918813,"Posted: 9 January, 2015",all,Robot Gandhi Zenyatta,"On first glance you may not think this game isn't really fun.  It is.  I don't know enough about computer processing to explain the details you need to get this game to run smooth, all I can tell you is that it runs beautifully on my Windows Surface Pro 3.  What I can tell you is that it is a whitty game that breaks the fourth-wall (For those of you who don't know:The Fourth Wall is a term in entertainment when the character has a thought about the watcher, or user sometimes in the form of ""I wonder if this is some kind of games and we are all just pawns""  or the characters just outright acknowledge you as a player in a sense that you aren't apart of their universe)  It can be quite fun, and is a good time waster if your at work and want two hours to kill.  The singleplayer is mainly versing higher level intelligence bots, not much to it, but if your that type of person thats easy to please, and doesnt need complexity it can be really enjoyable.  Also I do know it takes a long time to find a match in PvP.  If you play with a friend it is better.  Overall  the fact that this game is a time-waster (in a goodway) and has achievements is great!  I personally like to achievement hunt, but the fact that a smaller game with not so difficult achievements gives me a break, and its just interesting to see what objectives the game will amek you complete.   However, if you are not good with focus, or multitasking I DO NOT reccomend this game for you as you will get frustrated with trying to build and upgrade defenses, also trying to make them into a maze.  Dispatch troops, and upgrade that aswell. And finally trying to upgrade your gold mines and castles at the same time."
